snippet.textDisplay:
I'm still astonished that the Seahawks coach Pete Carroll decided to punt after Wilson was sacked for a loss late in the game. I'm certain Wilson and Seahawk's clutch offense could have could have gotten a first down and scored in the few remaining minutes,they were doing so well in the second half or perhaps not, but you have to try because if you need to score
with only minutes remaining the absolute last thing you do is turn the ball over to Aaron Rodgers no matter how good your defense is, no, no no friggin way do you do that. You keep him on the sidelines as much as possible. You don't that in any game let alone a playoff.I still can't believe Carroll's decision.
